<h5 style="text-align:center;" data-zesty-id="content:text:32:93">WHO WE ARE &amp; WHAT WE DO</h5>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:33:29">
	SAWA is the volunteer, educational and fundraising arm of The Salvation Army of Greenville, SC, supporting initiatives that enrich the lives of those individuals living in in our community by meeting them at their point of need.
</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:34:22">
	As a member of SAWA, you are among Greenville's most influential and active community leaders, women with a generous spirit and determination to be “doing the most good." Meetings are held on the 2nd Wednesday of each month (except July) at 11:30 a.m. at the Kroc Center located at 42 Westfield Street in Greenville (lunch is served).&nbsp;&nbsp;Members have many opportunities throughout the year to volunteer and attend social events and meetings.
</p>
